==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|sacramentum|sacrāmentum|sacrament|lang=la}}, from {{term|sacro|sacrō|hallow, consecrate|lang=la}}, from {{term|sacer||sacred, holy|lang=la}}, originally sum deposited by parties to a suit.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{Christianity}} A sacred act or ceremony in [[Christianity]].  In Roman Catholic theology, a '''sacrament''' is defined as "an outward sign instituted by Christ to give grace."

